                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note, hardly readable, is written in red ink which is fade
                              off. It mentions Walda Krǝstos (which is his name after consecration
                              as priest, sǝmä kǝhnätu) and his relatives. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Short hymns and supplications (ʾaryām, mawāśǝʾt, mǝlṭān,
                           etc.), performed for the funeral of different categories of Christians
                              (<locus target="#120ra">120ra</locus> l.17 – 122rb l.22) are written
                           in smaller script.
 - Pen trials (the bottom one dated "Monday,
                           Gǝnbot 28"): <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>. 
 - Minor notes in the
                           upper margin: <locus target="#8r">8r</locus>, 11v, 13v, 17v, 20v, 24r,
                           37r, 42r, 46r, 48r, 49r, 55v, 58v, 60v, 65v, 71v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- (Recent?) coloured threads and strips of textile
                              are inserted in the upper corners of some fols. (e.g., fols. 58,
                              65).</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
